-- Kuwait’s Aref Energy Holders Back Acquisition Offer, KUNA Says
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2012-05-31T04:33:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/kuwait-s-aref-energy-holders-back-acquisition-offer-kuna-says.html
Aref Energy Holding (AREFENRG)  KSCC shareholders
approved an offer by Development Enterprises Holding, a unit of
 Kuwait Finance House (KFIN) , to acquire the company’s shares, state-run
 KUNA  news agency reported.  Aref Energy, a unit of Aref Investment Group, hired a
consultant to evaluate the company assets and shares, KUNA said,
citing a statement from Aref Energy. The consultant has set 126
fils for each share and Kuwait Finance has offered 134 fils, it
said. There are 1,000 fils to the Kuwaiti dinar.  Kuwait Clearing Co. will oversee the acquisition “which
will take hold within 30 days as of June 3,” according to KUNA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
 fmacdonald4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
